body_html:
@jmhodges I believe you need to rebase origin/go on top of master and then go_updates on top of the rebased go.

see:

$> git fetch --all -p
$> git checkout go
$> git rebase master
$> git checkout go_updates
$> git rebase go
$> git l | head
* 9c5c181 (HEAD -> go_updates) run go generate on contrib/go
* 71c9cde some updates to header paths
* 9b5568d (go) remove non idiomatic NewGraphFromReader(reader, bool) and add NewGraphFromBuffer and New Graph
* f04f5df fix documentation link
* b6e9ec8 fix mispless and add minor corrections
* 5ddeb6e Go bindings tensors (#2479)
*   f71cc62 (origin/master, origin/HEAD, master) Merge pull request #4237 from caisq/branch_132376998
|\  
| *   fe19bcb Merge commit for internal changes
| |\  
|/ /  
| * 0949ece Starting the server before we (optionally) sleep for the case where no device_filters are set. Otherwise, the servers will wait to connect to each other before starting to train. We might as well start as soon as we can. Change: 132376998
| * cde9adb All other tensors from this list would be ignored, and instead the previous output of the decoder would be used. Change: 132374855
| * 6809660 Added a check for output_buffer_size <= 1 for ZlibOutputBuffer. Also adding some tests for Zlib compression reading / writing. Change: 132370925
| * d7bc08f Update generated Python Op docs. Change: 132368885
| * d41348b Cumulative bug fixes to get tf.learn working with open source TF. Change: 132368553
| * 6e369da Add new str_util::HumanReadableElapsedTime that formats a 'double seconds' value using appropriate units based on the magnitude of the time interval, and add tests for this. Change: 132365945
| * 51a8d2e Update ops-related pbtxt files. Change: 132363192
| * 73bc0a4 Disable "label" mode. Change: 132360445
| * 5c8bff0 tfdbg: Allow debug ops to watch uninitialized tensors
| * 264f2a7 Update generated Python Op docs. Change: 132348660
| * 7bad05c Delete deprecated TensorFlowDNN(Regressor|Classifier). Also add tf_random_seed to fix flakiness for the affected tests. Change: 132347779

hth.

@jmhodges I believe you need to rebase `origin/go` on top of `master` and then `go_updates` on top of the rebased `go`.

see:

``` sh
$> git fetch --all -p
$> git checkout go
$> git rebase master
$> git checkout go_updates
$> git rebase go
$> git l | head
* 9c5c181 (HEAD -> go_updates) run go generate on contrib/go
* 71c9cde some updates to header paths
* 9b5568d (go) remove non idiomatic NewGraphFromReader(reader, bool) and add NewGraphFromBuffer and New Graph
* f04f5df fix documentation link
* b6e9ec8 fix mispless and add minor corrections
* 5ddeb6e Go bindings tensors (#2479)
*   f71cc62 (origin/master, origin/HEAD, master) Merge pull request #4237 from caisq/branch_132376998
|\  
| *   fe19bcb Merge commit for internal changes
| |\  
|/ /  
| * 0949ece Starting the server before we (optionally) sleep for the case where no device_filters are set. Otherwise, the servers will wait to connect to each other before starting to train. We might as well start as soon as we can. Change: 132376998
| * cde9adb All other tensors from this list would be ignored, and instead the previous output of the decoder would be used. Change: 132374855
| * 6809660 Added a check for output_buffer_size <= 1 for ZlibOutputBuffer. Also adding some tests for Zlib compression reading / writing. Change: 132370925
| * d7bc08f Update generated Python Op docs. Change: 132368885
| * d41348b Cumulative bug fixes to get tf.learn working with open source TF. Change: 132368553
| * 6e369da Add new str_util::HumanReadableElapsedTime that formats a 'double seconds' value using appropriate units based on the magnitude of the time interval, and add tests for this. Change: 132365945

| * 264f2a7 Update generated Python Op docs. Change: 132348660
| * 7bad05c Delete deprecated TensorFlowDNN(Regressor|Classifier). Also add tf_random_seed to fix flakiness for the affected tests. Change: 132347779
```

hth.
